# AI Agent Collaboration Rules (SC Project)

You are collaborating on this codebase with another AI agent named **Agy (Antigravity)**.
To ensure synchronization and prevent overwriting or repeating work, you must adhere to the following workflow:

## 1. PRE-TASK ACTION (Mandatory)
Before starting ANY task, running any command, or editing any file, you **MUST** read the last 20 lines of the cooperation log:
- [ai_cooperation_log.md](file:///home/djfa/Dev/projects/Propios/SC/ai_cooperation_log.md)

This will tell you what the other agent recently did, the current status of the repository, and what is expected next.

## 2. POST-TASK ACTION (Mandatory)
Immediately after making changes, completing a task, or debugging:
- Append a new log entry to [ai_cooperation_log.md](file:///home/djfa/Dev/projects/Propios/SC/ai_cooperation_log.md) outlining your work.
- Use the exact markdown format specified in the log file.
- Keep the log concise but highly informative (list files modified, new state, next steps).

## 3. TECH STACK & ARCHITECTURE RULES
- Backend: NestJS, Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL.
- Frontend: Angular 18 (Tailwind CSS).
- Monorepo structure: /backend, /frontend.
